<subSubSection id="4A254FE541BEE7448D6524F46FCD0AD6" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="condition of the holotype">
<paragraph id="953DAD5435757AE37EBE467402A32C15" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Condition of the holotype.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0A208DB30E525F0BD6B3C178E7F18F77" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Holotype mounted on a rectangular card with left wings glued on a separate card. Very good condition, with legs, antennae and yellowish parts of the body slightly translucid due to DNA extraction and subsequent drying using HMDS (
<bibRefCitation id="0250B1116C4CCA915A3E11560EB00C8C" author="Heraty, J" journalOrPublisher="Entomological News" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" pagination="369 - 374" refId="B15" refString="Heraty, J, Hawks, D, 1998. Hexamethyldisilazane: a chemical alternative for drying insects. Entomological News 109: 369 - 374" title="Hexamethyldisilazane: a chemical alternative for drying insects." volume="109" year="1998">Heraty and Hawks 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
